org.wattdepot.server

Class WattDepot

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.wattdepot.server.WattDepot
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    WattDepotImpl

    public abstract class WattDepot
extends Object
    WattDepot persistence abstract interface. Different persistence implementations should subclass this class and implement their persistence schemes.
    Author:
    Cam Moore

      • defineCollectorMetaData

        public abstract CollectorMetaData defineCollectorMetaData(String id,
                                        Sensor sensor,
                                        Long pollingInterval,
                                        String depositoryId,
                                        UserGroup owner)
                                                   throws UniqueIdException,
                                                          MissMatchedOwnerException
        Defines a new CollectorMetaData. This does not start any processes.
        Parameters:
        id - The unique id.
        sensor - The Sensor to poll.
        pollingInterval - The polling interval.
        depositoryId - The id of the depository to use.
        owner - the owner of the CollectorMetaData.
        Returns:
        The defined CollectorMetaData.
        Throws:
        UniqueIdException - if the id is already used for another CollectorMetaData.
        MissMatchedOwnerException - if the given owner doesn't match the owners of the Sensor or Depository.

                                       throws UniqueIdException
        Defines a new Location in WattDepot.
        Parameters:
        id - The unique id.

        longitude - The decimal Longitude.

        description - A String description of the Location.
        owner - The owner of the Location.
        Returns:

        Throws:
